    "language_status": "Stable design",
    "notes": "Parameter and capture modes are explicit. An ordinary `mut name: T` parameter acquires its argument once and commits a callee-owned mutable local: it creates no caller alias or write-back edge, and a failure before commit retains the caller owner. `inout` instead borrows one caller place exclusively for the dynamic call extent and successful writes remain visible in that place. borrow creates a nonescaping shared region view; move transfers ownership and invalidates the source. The narrow Stable profile permits replacement through an inout place but not moving the current value out of that borrowed place; definite reinitialization across every exit is not a current feature. Overlapping inout/borrow conflicts, use-after-move, escape across return/storage/capture, and crossing suspension or actor transfer without an admitted ownership proof are rejected.",
